Technologies :-
Java/j2ee,  jsp,  Spring web mvc, Spring jdbc, mysql, tomcat, eclipse.
Mysql- Db Creation :
1)	Table  Name : Employee
Columns :   Empcode (pk), Empname, Designation, Salaray,mobile,email, DeptId (FK), UserId, CreateTime (DateTime)
2)	 Table  Name : DeptName
Columns:   DeptId (PK),  DeptName,Userid,CreateTime(DateTime)

3)	Table Name :  UserTbl
Columns :  UserId(pk),  UserName, UserPwd, Staus  (Yes/No), RoleId
  Role id  1 For Admin User
  Role id  -2  For Employee
  Roled id  3 For Manager

Insert Related Data  Only in UserTbl,  using Sql Query from Command Prompt .

1)	Create Login Page
2)	On Successful full of Login, depending on User Role, Admin Page / Employee /Manager Pages should be displayed
Admin page:-
1)	Display menu
a)	Create departments
b)	Create employee
c)	Display list of employees grid (Data Tables need to be used ). 
d)	Search the employees by(user name, mobile, email,designation)
(enter the any one or more fields then press the search button then display the search data)
Preferred  Spring Rest Calls for the Above
And Should use Jquery and Ajax for Dynamic Data Display.
Employee page:-
1)	Display menu
a)	Emp profile, with Pic
Manager Page:-
1)	Display menu
a)	Manager  profile

